Rugby including Super Rugby, The Rugby Championship, International Tests, NRL
The Rugby Championship is an International rugby union competition that is contested each year by Australia, Argentina, New Zealand and South Africa.
The Rugby Championship is considered to be the toughest rugby competition in the world.
The games between Australia and New Zealand also go towards determining the winner of the Bledisloe Cup. The Freedom Cup is contested by New Zealand and South Africa, and the Mandela Challenge Plate between Australia and South Africa.
Watch all 12 games live and exclusive on Setanta Sports throughout August and September.